claim.claim-text:
17. A system for validating client computing devices in a network game environment, the system comprising:
a monitoring module stored in a computer-readable storage medium and executable by a processor to passively monitor game data received from one or more client computing devices executing a network game over a network, the game data being received as a part of network game play without requiring the one or more client computing devices to execute instructions apart from the network game play;
a rules library stored in memory and comprising one or more game metrics associated with the network game;
an analysis engine stored in the computer-readable storage medium and executable by the processor to access the one or more game metrics from the rules library stored in the memory, wherein execution of the analysis engine determines whether the received game data complies with at least one of the accessed one or more game metrics; and
a query engine stored in the computer-readable storage medium and executable by the processor to generate and pose at least one query to the one or more client computing devices whose game data fails to comply with the at least one of the accessed one or more game metrics, and wherein the analysis engine is further executable to identify that a response received from the one or more queried client computing devices indicates that the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one of the one or more accessed game metrics is authorized and determine that the one or more client computing devices are validated for continued network game play when the received game data from the one or more client computing devices does not correspond to the at least one of the one or more accessed game metrics, the determination based on the response to the at least one query, the response being sent from the one or more client computing devices and indicating that the game data that does not correspond to the at least one of the one or more accessed game metrics is authorized.

18. A method for validating devices in a gaming network, the method comprising:
monitoring one or more devices interacting with a network game in the gaming network at a computing device tasked with validating the one or more monitored devices in the gaming network;
passively receiving game data from the one or more monitored devices at the tasked computing device, the passive data receipt occurring as a part of network game play without requiring the one or more monitored devices to execute instructions apart from the network game play;
evaluating the passively received game data in conjunction with at least one game metric associated with the network game at the tasked computing device;
determining that the passively received game data does not adhere to the at least one game metric; and
initiating a validation sequence, the validation sequence determining that the one or more monitored devices are valid for continued network game play when the passively received game data does not adhere to the at least one game metric, wherein the validation sequence comprises:
generating a query to the one or more monitored devices that generated the passively received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric,
sending the query to the one or more monitored devices that generated the passively received game data,
identifying that a response received from the one or more queried devices indicates that the passively received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized, and
determining that the one or more queried devices are valid for continued network game play when the passively received game data from the one or more queried devices does not correspond to the at least one game metric, the determination based on the response to the query indicating that the passively received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized.

19. The method of claim 18, wherein the validation sequence comprises:
selecting one or more additional game metrics associated with the network game;
receiving additional game data from the one or more monitored devices that generated the passively received game data that does not adhere to the at least one game metric;
evaluating the additional received game data in conjunction with the one or more additional game metrics associated with the network game; and
ejecting from the gaming network any of the one or more monitored devices whose additional received game data does not adhere to the one or more additional game metrics associated with the network game.

20. A non-transitory machine-readable storage medium having embodied thereon a program executable by a machine to perform a method for validating devices in a gaming network, the method comprising:
monitoring one or more devices interacting with a network game in the gaming network;
receiving game data from the one or more monitored devices, wherein the game data is received as a part of a passive data exchange, the passive data exchange occurring as a part of network game play and without requiring the one or more monitored devices to execute instructions apart from the network game play;
evaluating the received game data in conjunction with at least one game metric associated with the network game;
determining that the received game data does not adhere to the at least one game metric; and
initiating a validation sequence of the one or more monitored devices, the validation sequence determining that the one or more monitored devices are valid for continued network game play when the received game data does not adhere to the at least one game metric, wherein the validation sequence comprises:
sending a query to the one or more monitored devices that generated the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric,
identifying that a response received from the one or more queried devices indicates that the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized, and
determining that the one or more queried devices is valid for continued network game play when the received game data from the one or more queried devices does not correspond to the at least one game metric, the determination based on the response to the query indicating that the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized.

21. A non-transitory machine-readable storage medium having embodied thereon a program executable by a machine to perform a method for validating devices in a gaming network, the method comprising:
receiving game data generated by at least one device in the gaming network, wherein the game data is received as a part of a passive data exchange, the at least one device configured for execution of a network game, the passive data exchange occurring as a part of network game play and without requiring the at least one device to execute instructions apart from the network game play;
identifying at least one game metric from a library of game metrics, the identified game metric associated with the received game data;
identifying at least one aspect of the received game data that does not adhere to the at least one game metric identified from the library of game metrics;
sending at least one query to the at least one device that generated the received game data that does not adhere to the at least one game metric;
receiving a response to the at least one query, the response being sent from the at least one queried device;
identifying that the response received from the at least one queried device indicates that the at least one identified aspect of the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized; and
determining that the at least one queried device is valid for continued network game play when the received game data from the at least one queried device does not adhere to the at least one game metric, the determination based on the response to the at least one query indicating that the at least one identified aspect of the received game data that does not correspond to the at least one game metric is authorized.
